value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the process of creating protein polymers.
Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the process of creating protein polymers.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the process of creating protein polymers.
The regulated release of a gonadotropin, any hormone that stimulates the gonads, especially follicle-stimulating hormone and luteinizing hormone.
The regulated release of luteinizing hormone, a gonadotropic glycoprotein hormone secreted by the anterior pituitary.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a gonadotropin.
Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a gonadotropin.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a gonadotropin.
The process in which the wraps of cell membrane that constitute myelin are laid down around an axon in the central or peripheral nervous system.
The process in which the wraps of cell membrane that constitute myelin are laid down around an axon by an oligodendrocyte in the central nervous system.
The process in which the wraps of cell membrane that constitute myelin are laid down around an axon by Schwann cells in the peripheral nervous system.

label.value: axon ensheathment in central nervous system

value.value: The process in which a glial cell membrane closes around an axon in the central nervous system. This can be a myelinating or a non-myelinating neuron-glial interaction.
The process in which a Schwann cell membrane closes around an axon in the peripheral nervous system. This can be a myelinating or a non-myelinating neuron-glial interaction.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte differentiation.
Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte differentiation.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte differentiation.

The chemical reactions and pathways involving aldosterone, a corticosteroid hormone that is produced by the zona glomerulosa of the adrenal cortex and regulates salt (sodium and potassium) and water balance.

The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of aldosterone, a corticosteroid hormone that is produced by the zona glomerulosa of the adrenal cortex and regulates salt (sodium and potassium) and water balance.

The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of aldosterone, a corticosteroid hormone that is produced by the zona glomerulosa of the adrenal cortex and regulates salt (sodium and potassium) and water balance.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving aldosterone.

label.value: negative regulation of aldosterone metabolic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving aldosterone.

label.value: positive regulation of aldosterone metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving aldosterone.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of aldosterone.

label.value: negative regulation of aldosterone biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of aldosterone.

label.value: positive regulation of aldosterone biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of aldosterone.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving any hormone.

label.value: negative regulation of hormone metabolic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving any hormone.

label.value: positive regulation of hormone metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving any hormone.

label.value: negative regulation of hormone biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of hormones.

Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of stimulus by estradiol, a C18 steroid hormone hydroxylated at C3 and C17 that acts as a potent estrogen.
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of oxygen within a cell.
The directed movement of lipids within cells.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids within cells.

label.value: negative regulation of intracellular lipid transport

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids within cells.

label.value: positive regulation of intracellular lipid transport

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids within cells.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.
Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.

Combining with an MHC class Ib protein complex and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity. Class Ib here refers to non-classical class I molecules, such as those of the CD1 or HLA-E gene families.

definition.value: Note that this term is intended for annotation of gene products that act as receptors for MHC class Ib protein complexes, not for components of the MHC class Ib protein complexes themselves.

value.value: Any process in which a melanosome is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within the cell.
The directed movement of a melanosome to a specific location.
The directed movement of melanosomes into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.
Any process that modulates the activity of a transporter.
Any process that stops or reduces the activity of a transporter.
Any process that activates or increases the activity of a transporter.

label.value: regulation of monoatomic ion transmembrane transporter activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the activity of an ion transporter.

label.value: negative regulation of ion transmembrane transporter activity

value.value: Any process that stops or reduces the activity of an ion transporter.
